Document: AudioEffectHardLimiter  
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffecthardlimiter.rst  
Summary: A limiter that prevents audio signals from exceeding a specified volume threshold to avoid clipping and distortion.  

A "limiter" disallows audio signals from exceeding a given volume threshold level in dB. Hard limiters predict volume peaks and will smoothly apply gain reduction when a peak crosses the ceiling threshold level to prevent clipping. It preserves the waveform and prevents it from crossing the ceiling threshold level. Adding one in the Master bus is recommended as a safety measure to prevent sudden volume peaks from occurring, and to prevent distortion caused by clipping, when the volume exceeds 0 dB. If clipping is desired, consider AudioEffectDistortion.MODE_CLIP. Note: Clipping should only be used intentionally to avoid unintended audio distortion.
---CHUNK---
