Document: AudioEffectHardLimiter
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffecthardlimiter.rst
Summary: Properties of the AudioEffectHardLimiter class, including ceiling_db, pre_gain_db, and release with their default values.

Property: ceiling_db (float): Controls the maximum output level before clipping. Default: -0.3
Property: pre_gain_db (float): Applies gain before limiting to compensate for signal loss. Default: 0.0
Property: release (float): Determines how quickly the limiter recovers after clipping. Default: 0.1
---CHUNK---
Document: AudioEffectHardLimiter  
Path: godot/classes/class_audioeffecthardlimiter.rst  
Summary: Properties for controlling audio limiting behavior, including ceiling level, pre-gain, and release time.  

ceiling_db (float): The waveform's maximum allowed value, in dB. This value can range from -24 to 0. Default: -0.3. Note: The default value of -0.3 prevents potential inter-sample peaks (ISP) from crossing over 0 dB, which can cause slight distortion on some older hardware. Set/Get: set_ceiling_db(value: float), get_ceiling_db() → float.  

pre_gain_db (float): Gain before limiting, in dB. Value can range from -24 to 24. Default: 0.0. Set/Get: set_pre_gain_db(value: float), get_pre_gain_db() → float.  

release (float): Time it takes in seconds for the gain reduction to fully release. Value can range from 0.01 to 3.0. Default: 0.1. Set/Get: set_release(value: float), get_release() → float.